---
layout: base
title: A11Y Websites
meta_title: Home
description: "Showcase of accessible websites"
pagination:
  data: collections.posts
  size: 5
  alias: posts
---

<article class="page">
    <header class="page__header">
        <h1 class="page__title">
            A11Y Websites
        </h1>
        <h2 class="page__description lead">{{ description | safe }}.</h2>
        <p>These websites have been assessed through both automated and manual testing against the success criteria set out in the Website Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 to grade AA and above.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="page__content">
        
        {% if posts.length %}
            <ul class="cards">
                {% for post in posts %}
                    <li>
                        {% include "post.njk" %}
                    </li>
                {% endfor %}
            </ul>

            {% if collections.posts.length > pagination.size %}
                <nav class="pagination" aria-label="Pagination links">
                    {% if pagination.href.previous %}
                    <a class="nav__link" href="{{ pagination.href.previous }}" data-direction="backwards">{% icon "arrow" %}Newer features</a>{% endif %}
                    {% if pagination.href.next %}<a class="nav__link" href="{{ pagination.href.next }}" data-direction="forwards">Later features{% icon "arrow" %}</a>{% endif %}
                </nav>
            {% endif %} 

        {% else %}
            <p>No websites yet.</p>
        {% endif %}

        <a class="nav__link nav__center" href="#header" data-direction="up">{% icon "arrow" %}Back to top of page</a>

    </div>
</article>